HEADWORD: Carnify
<hw>Car"ni*fy</hw> <pr>(k⟦aum⟧r"n⟦icr⟧*f⟦imac⟧)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<ety>[LL. <ets>carnificare</ets>, fr. L. <ets>caro</ets>,
<ets>carnis</ets>, flesh + <ets>facere</ets> to make: cf. F.
<ets>carnifier</ets>.]</ety> <def>To form flesh; to become like
flesh.</def> <rj><au>Sir M. Hale.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
